cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.SD 

This paper deals with the task of automatically detecting disease outbreaks from online news articles, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as text mining and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of different algorithms for aberration detection, which falls under the scope of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper also touches upon issues related to data bias and reporting, which could be relevant to cs.SD (Sound).
